22/07/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- IMF representatives said Monday (21 July) that the Bulgarian government should adhere to the three-year fiscal programme.
The mission is in the country for the 3rd quarterly review under the stand-by arrangement with the Fund.
Noting that the economy has performed well, the representatives said compliance with the fiscal programme is essential to preserving political stability.
(Dnevnik, Trud, Pari - 22/07/03;
BTA, BNT - 21/07/03)
